She doesn't even use a pottery much.
In her wooden house in Enarotali, the capital of Paniai County, in the rebel Indonesian province of Papua, the housewife usually simply puts sweet potatoes, which is called "nota," right in the middle of the house.
Half an hour later, the charred tuber is taken out and eaten with impatient, unwashed hands.
Degei sits on the ground floor - she doesn't have any furniture - and that's where she does her housework, like washing clothes with murky water from a nearby swamp.
