In a few minutes, Green thanks the audience, and suddenly it's over.
Actors drop ropes off their necks and wipe tears.
Bradshaw hugs Marbo, the man in the suit who played the main doll.
Nick Raskona hugs the other two actors and suddenly, crying, falls into their arms: the emotional burden of the show finally fell on him.
"It's all right," whispers one of the women.
