Some of the wealthiest West Midland homeowners are once again in conflict with the strong Roma who have overcome the mortuary dug by the municipal authorities to reoccupy the field next to their homes.
The Gypsy parked 20 houses on wheels in a field bordering the rich street of Solichalla, which is jokingly known as the millionaire street.
With horses, babies and lots of houses on wheels, they came back after they were kicked out no later than May, and they were not prevented by a moat dug out by the municipal authorities to prevent their invasion.
