In Ukraine, Russians were asked to go to prison for illegal border crossing
The Verkhovna Rada has registered a draft law under which criminal penalties may be imposed on Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to RT, the document registered in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament implies a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained at the arms border, the time of his detention would increase to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians attempting to enter Russia outside the designated crossing points.
